2500|$|Shepherd {{then went}} on to form a new band, The Monarchs (initially known as The Honkies), {{together}} with Andy Kelly on bass (Glide), Greg Hitchcock on guitar (The Neptunes, The Kryptonics, New Christs, The Verys, Challenger 7, You Am I, The Dearhunters) and his brother Murray Shepherd (Harpoon, The <b>Fun</b> <b>Things,</b> Screaming Tribesmen) on drums. The Monarchs played with The Meanies, Even, You Am I, Joe Strummer and The Hellacopters. In August 2000 they released their first single, [...] "2001" [...] b/w [...] "This Is All I Can Do" [...] (Ivy League Records) which was followed by their debut album, Make Yer Own Fun, in October 2001 (Shock Records).|$|E
