2500|$|Siddhartha Lal, after {{completing}} his education {{started working with}} MAN Nutzfahrzeuge AG. He joined Eicher Group in 1999, working in various capacities in the Eicher tractor division, and then became CEO of Royal Enfield in 2000 (at the age of 26) aiming to end the unit's losses. From 2000 to 2004, he worked out of Royal Enfield's headquarters in Chennai, introducing cost-cutting measures and product upgrades. [...] "Honestly, at age 26, it seemed a <b>fun</b> <b>thing</b> to do. I could eat, sleep, ride and talk motorcycles," [...] Siddhartha said in a 2015 interview.|$|R
