5000|$|Hickson's {{breakthrough}} role {{came in the}} 2016 action-comedy Deadpool, {{her first}} speaking part. She played Meghan Orlovsky, a girl whom the titular character assists. In an interview, Hickson noted that the scale of this movie, along with her speaking role, greatly increased her passion for acting. [...] "I didn't really know how badly I wanted to work as an actor until Deadpool," [...] she said. She further stated that prior to Deadpool, [...] "I thought acting might just be a <b>fun</b> <b>thing</b> I did on the side. That {{was the thing that}} changed my life." ...|$|R
5000|$|It {{was almost}} like a Manhattan Projectfor songwriters," [...] says Bern. [...] "It was the most <b>fun</b> <b>thing</b> I've ever done. Dan Bern, 2007 The cast and crew {{recorded}} 40 original songs; 33 are featured in the movie. Singer-songwriter Dan Bern and Mike Viola (of the Candy Butchers) wrote most of the film's songs, including [...] "There's a Change A' Happenin'", [...] "The Mulatto Song" [...] and [...] "Hole in My Pants". Marshall Crenshaw wrote the title tune and Van Dyke Parks penned one of the 1960-styled psychedelic jams, [...] "Black Sheep".|$|R
